  "text": "Found 4 REST storage providers in pkg/registry/ that define both v1beta1Storage() and v1Storage() methods: storage (storage_storage.go), admissionregistration (storage_apiserver.go), authentication (storage_authentication.go), and resource (storage_resource.go). Each provider's NewRESTStorage() method calls these version-specific methods to populate VersionedResourcesStorageMap entries for v1beta1 and v1 API versions. The StorageVersion Manager interface is defined in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storageversion/manager.go with methods AddResourceInfo, UpdateStorageVersions, PendingUpdate, LastUpdateError, and Completed. The ResourceEncodingConfig interface and DefaultResourceEncodingConfig implementation in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go control which GroupVersion is used for etcd storage via StorageEncodingFor() and BackwardCompatibileStorageEncodingFor(), with SetResourceEncoding() allowing per-resource overrides. The emulatedStorageVersion() function handles compatibility version selection. MergeResourceEncodingConfigs in resourceconfig/helpers.go applies resource encoding overrides. The StorageFactory interface in storage_factory.go provides the top-level storage location abstraction. The updater.go file implements the actual storage version update logic against the apiserverinternal API.",
